    "rule_id": "MLA9-R1.3",
    "source": "MLA Handbook 9th Edition, Section 2.1",
    "category": "author_formatting",
    "description": "For TWO authors: use 'and' between names (second name NOT inverted). This differs from APA's use of '&' and from incorrectly inverting both names. The word 'and' is preferred in MLA for its formality and readability.",
    "examples": [
      {
        "type": "correct",
